275. quodcumque fluit . . .: according to Epicurus every sensa- tion, every mental expression, is the result of touch or modified touch. Exact images or fine films (simulacra, εἴδωλα) are thrown off from the surface of solid objects (στερέμνια) and are perceived by the soul-atoms in the bodily organs or by the mind itself. These films move infinitely fast and incessantly flow off from bodies, yet the bodies only diminish slowly‚ so fine are they. A mixture of these films makes us believe we see centaurs, chimaeras, sirens, sea-serpents‚ &c.
